<recipe>
	<title>Venezuelan chocolate chicken</title>
	<description>This traditional South American chicken dish incorporates chocolate to give it a unique and authentic flavour. Served with crispy fried corn cachapas</description>
	<source>http://www.mnn.com/food/recipes/photos/5-spicy-chocolate-dishes/venezuelan-chocolate-chicken</source>
	<source>http://www.food.com/recipe/jimmys-cachapas-203128</source>
	<image>http://www.mnn.com/sites/default/files/styles/featured_blog/public/venezuelan_chicken.jpg</image>
	<author>Paul Young</author>
	<cooking>0:30</cooking>
	<preparation>0:30</preparation>
	<difficulty>easy</difficulty>
	<serves>4</serves>
	<date>18 June 2014</date>
	<genre type="region">South America/Venezuela</genre>
	<genre type="ingredient">meat/chicken</genre>
	<genre type="style">casserole</genre>
	<ingredients>
		<item id="1">vegetable oil</item>
		<item id="2">garlic</item>
		<item id="3">shallot(s)</item>
		<item id="4">chicken thigh(s) or thigh fillet(s)</item>
		<item id="5">valencia orange(s)</item>
		<item id="6">jalapeno chilli(es)</item>
		<item id="7">dried ancho chilli(es)</item>
		<item id="8">coriander seed(s)</item>
		<item id="9">diced canned tomato(s)</item>
		<item id="10">brown sugar</item>
		<item id="11">70% cacao darck chocolate</item>
		<item id="12">fresh coriander leaf/leaves</item>
		<item id="13">canned sweetcorn</item>
		<item id="14">milk</item>
		<item id="15">salt</item>
		<item id="16">black pepper</item>
		<item id="17">egg(s)</item>
		<item id="18">finely ground cornmeal</item>
		<item id="19">butter</item>
	</ingredients>
	<dish>
		<name>chocolate chicken</name>
		<step>Preheat oven to 200&#160;&#176;C. Heat [oil|1.1] on a heavy-bottomed frying pan over a medium-high heat. Add the [garlic|2.1] and [shalots|3.1] and fry until tender.</step>
		<step>Brown the [chicken|4.1] on each site, for about 10 minutes, then add [orange juice and zest|5.1], [fresh|6.1] and [dried chillies|7.1], [coriander seeds|8.1] [tomatoes|9.1] and [sugar|10.1]. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, then cook in the oven for a further 20 minutes.</step>
		<step>Remove the pan from the oven and set the chicken aside. Add the [chocolate pieces|11.1] to the pan and stir until blended, at which point you will have a dark, gravy-like sauce. Return the chicken to the pan, ready for serving with the cachapas and [coriander|12.1]</step>
		<ingredient id="1.1">
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="2.1">
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<unit>clove(s)</unit>
			<prep>minced</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="3.1">
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<prep>finely chpped</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="4.1">
			<quantity>500</quantity>
			<unit>g</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="5.1">
			<quantity>3</quantity>
			<prep>juiced and zested</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="6.1">
			<quantity>3</quantity>
			<prep>chopped and seeded</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="7.1">
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<prep>shredded and seeded</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="8.1">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="9.1">
			<quantity>400</quantity>
			<unit>g</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="10.1">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="11.1">
			<quantity>85</quantity>
			<unit>g</unit>
			<prep>broken into pieces</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="12.1">
			<quantity>4</quantity>
			<unit>sprig(s)</unit>
			<prep>roughly chopped</prep>
		</ingredient>
	</dish>
	<dish>
		<name>cachapas</name>
		<step>In a food processor, puree the [corn|13.1] with [milk|14.1], [sugar|10.2], [salt|15.1], [pepper|16.1], [egg|17.1] and [cornmeal|18.1]. The pancake should be the consistency of a thick pancake batter.</step>
		<step>Heat a large non-stick frying panover a low heat and add some [butter|19.1]. When it is melted and is hot, add the batter, forming 10&#160;cm circles. Cook for 2 minutes on each side.</step>
		<ingredient id="13.1">
			<quantity>400</quantity>
			<unit>g</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="14.1">
			<quantity>0.25</quantity>
			<unit>cup(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="10.2">
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="15.1">
			<quantity>0.5</quantity>
			<unit>teaspoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="16.1">
			<quantity>0.25</quantity>
			<unit>teaspoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="17.1">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="18.1">
			<quantity>0.75</quantity>
			<unit>cup(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="19.1">
			<quantity>4</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
	</dish>
</recipe>